13/03/2003
BUCHAREST, Romania -- The transport ministry and the national railway company launched projects Wednesday (12 March) to modernise 20 train stations.
The programme attracted 76m euros in financing from the EBRD and First Credit Suisse Boston.
The stations are situated on major railway links to European capitals.
Construction companies will preserve the architecture of the buildings while updating the technology.
(Rompres, Mediafax - 12/03/03)
